      "content": "okay but \"carrying weight\" is a bit of a cop out isn't it? if we're talking about a moral hierarchy, most philosophical frameworks say that the right to life and bodily autonomy are the baseline. you can't really \"balance\" a person's survival against a government's paperwork/regulations without it sounding like you're saying the paperwork is just as important as the person. isn't it more accurate to say that the border security argument is essentially just an argument for legalism over morality?",
